KW  - Dynamic comparative advantage
KW  - Services
KW  - Industrialization
AB  - The goal of this paper is to examine the role of the service sector in the process of industrialization. We propose a model which recognizes that (non-traded) services are demanded by consumers as well as producers. Income increases thus lower production costs of industrial goods. The inclusion of non-traded services enables us to explain how a primary exporting economy can industrialize without resorting to protection. This paper can be construed as a formalization of some aspects of the Staple Theory of Growth.
