KW  - Labour markets
KW  - Wage determination
KW  - Ethnicity
AB  - We find evidence of ethnic fractionalization and its consequences in an African labour market. We consider earnings differentials between members of different ethnic groups and between employers' relatives, unrelated co-ethnics, and other workers in the Ghanaian manufacturing sector. Variations in a standard set of observed workers' characteristics explain a large proportion of the earnings differentials between ethnic groups. However, the greatest proportion is explained by the ethnic fractionalization of the labour market combined with variations in employers' characteristics. Workers who are related to their employers earn a premium and there is statistical discrimination in favour of inexperienced co-ethnic workers.
